    <p class="reveal"><strong>One-off sessions.</strong> Two hours. We come to you. Your team walks away with specific AI workflows for their roles. Good for companies who want to get everyone up to speed fast.</p>

    <p class="reveal"><strong>Subscription series.</strong> Ongoing monthly sessions. Each one builds on the last. New tools, new techniques, new workflows as AI keeps changing. Good for companies who want to stay current instead of catching up once a year.</p>

    <p class="reveal">Both start with a <a href="/contact/">free 20-minute call</a> where I learn what your team does and what tools you're already paying for. No pitch. Just figuring out if this makes sense for you.</p>


    <h2 class="reveal">The Math</h2>

    <p class="reveal">Say you have 10 employees. Each one wastes 30 minutes a day on tasks AI could handle. That's 5 hours a day. 25 hours a week. Over 100 hours a month.</p>

    <p class="reveal">At an average loaded cost of $30/hour, that's $3,000 a month in time you're already paying for. A two-hour training session costs a fraction of one month's waste. The ROI isn't theoretical. It's arithmetic.</p>


    <h2 class="reveal">The Real Question</h2>

    <p class="reveal">You're already paying for the AI. You're already paying for the employees. The only thing missing is the two hours that connects them.</p>

    <p class="reveal">Your team will figure it out eventually. Or somebody else's team will figure it out first.</p>

